note.p:
Pub. L. 113–54, title I, § 104, Nov. 27, 2013, 127 Stat. 597, provided that: “In promulgating any regulations to implement this title [enacting subpart 9 of part C of subchapter VII of this chapter and sections 353a–1 and 353b of this title, amending this section and sections 352, 353a, 352b, and 353c of this title, and enacting provisions set out as notes under section 301 of this title] (and the amendments made by this title), the Secretary of Health and Human Services shall— “(1) issue a notice of proposed rulemaking that includes the proposed regulation;
“(2) provide a period of not less than 60 calendar days for comments on the proposed regulation; and
“(3) publish the final regulation not more than 18 months following publication of the proposed rule and not less than 30 calendar days before the effective date of such final regulation.”
